# Cloudflare _redirects — one rule per line: <from> <to> <status>. First match wins,
# so specific rules go ABOVE their wildcards. 301 = permanent (passes link equity).
# Sources: old-site Search Console + legacy WordPress URLs.
#
# Trailing slashes: the Worker normalizes them for REAL pages (/work/ -> /work), but
# NOT for redirect sources — a bare `/foo` rule does NOT match `/foo/`. Old WordPress
# URLs were served WITH a trailing slash, so every vanity/project source below needs
# an explicit `/foo/` twin or Google's crawled slash-form 404s. (Splat rules like
# `/foo/*` already cover their own slash + subpaths, so they need no twin.)

