# --- Blog -> journal (catch-all; keep AFTER the specific /blog rules above) ---
# Destination is the /journal INDEX, never /journal/:splat — journal slugs do NOT
# match old blog slugs (only 3 posts exist), so :splat manufactured redirects to
# non-existent /journal/<old-slug> pages (a 301 -> 404, worse than a plain 404).
# This also catches every `.html` and trailing-slash blog form the bare specific
# rules above miss; those land here on the valid index.
/blog        /journal   301
/blog/*      /journal   301

